Saif ul-John, ``Sword of John'', referring to arguably most famous sword in Islamic history, belonging to both Muhammad, and later, John, Henry, and with which John slew a Makkan foot soldier, cleaving both his helmet and head, at the Battle of Uhud, and with which he (John) slew Amr, a ferocious and devastating Makkan soldier at the Battle of the Trench at Madinah.
